-- BP Bonds Due Next Year Are Trading at Distressed Levels, Trace Data Show
-- Shannon D. Harrington
-- 2010-06-16T15:22:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/bp-s-750-million-of-bonds-due-2011-trade-at-distressed-levels-trace-says.html

          
          
             BP Plcâ€™s $750 million of 1.55
percent notes due in 2011 traded at distressed levels, according
to Trace, the bond-price reporting system of the Financial
Industry Regulatory Authority.  
 The bonds, which traded the most on record yesterday, fell
1.875 cents to 90.375 cents on the dollar as of 11:13 a.m. in
New York, Trace data show.  
 The securities, which rose as high as 101.2 cents in
February, pay a spread of 1,001 basis points. Bonds with
relative yields of more than 1,000 basis points, or 10
percentage points, are considered distressed.  
